<h2 id="editors-notes">Editor‚Äôs notes</h2>

<p>Hey there friends! Here‚Äôs a lesson teaching you how to play Guy Clark‚Äôs song ‚ÄúMy Favorite Picture of You‚Äù ‚Äì which he released on his final studio album in 2013. This is a great song, with Clark describing the circumstances surrounding a spontaneous Polaroid taken of his wife a few decades ago. Musically, this features fingerstyle guitar played in a very casual manner ‚Äì¬†primarily focusing on a change from A7sus4 =&gt; A7 =&gt; Dadd6 =&gt; D. I‚Äôll explain how to play these chords, and give you plenty of tips on how to go about practicing this chords. In the back part of the lesson, I‚Äôll show you the rough tab of how I play things ‚Äì should you want to get a bit more advanced with it.</p>

<p>Note, you‚Äôll need a capo on 2nd fret if you want to play along with Guy Clark‚Äôs version. Willie Nelson‚Äôs 2019 cover of this song uses a capo on the 3rd fret.</p>

<p>Here‚Äôs my timestamps for this lesson:</p>

<ul>
  <li>0:00 Lesson overview</li>
  <li>3:08 Chord progression overview</li>
  <li>5:28 How to play the chords</li>
  <li>9:03 Playthrough: simple strums</li>
  <li>12:43 Playthrough: advanced tab</li>
  <li>20:39 Farewell &amp; final advice</li>
</ul>

<p>I hope you enjoy! If you‚Äôre hungry for more Guy Clark, I also have lessons for these songs:</p>

